title: Florence Price Documentary Featuring Music Faculty and Students to Be Shown (University of Arkansas)
text: ( Source : University of Arkansas ) Photo Submitted Photo Courtesy of UA Special Collections Library In 1933 Arkansas native Florence Price made music history as the first African-American woman whose music was performed by a major symphony
